{
  "doc_id": "36404",
  "text": "Finally, the DpmrC ugd pmrG triple mutant could not survive in soil (Fig. 3) , which is an environment that induces transcription of PmrA-activated genes [CITATION_1] , possibly because Fe(III) and Al(III) are the most abundant metals in soil [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . This defect may be exacerbated in mild-acid conditions, such as those created by acid rain, which accelerate the elution of Fe(III) and Al(III) from soil [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . This implicates the PmrA/PmrB system in microbial survival in non-host environments, which may aid Salmonella transmission to new hosts.",
